##Why is the health code so hard to unify for a person of six sizes?

Weixin Signal Wowjiemian

Function introduction, the interface news is China has the influence original financial and economic new media, only serves the independent thinking crowd

Image: Visual China

Reporter: Lu Keyan, She Xiaochen Editor: Wen Shuqi

“

Health Code is a test of city digital management ability.

”

“

Health Code is a test of city digital management ability.

”

In more and more cities, the three colors of red, yellow and green on the health code have become a decisive factor in whether a person can return to school and work.

Since the beginning of February, tencent and Ali have launched health code related services in Shenzhen, Hangzhou and other places. Residents in the Declaration ID card, address, health status, contact history, travel history and other information, will be given a color health code.

The health code serves two main purposes. On the one hand, it is a certificate for citizens to enter and leave public places, and it is also a necessary condition for most of them to go back to work and study. On the other hand, enterprises and communities deal with different people according to the color classification of the health code and carry out precise control.

Every city's health code has a set of rules. In the case of Hangzhou, after a systematic analysis of personal information, a color code will be obtained. Among them, Green Code can pass in the city, Red Code and Yellow Code to implement 14 days and 7 days of concentration or home quarantine, in this period of continuous declaration of health and normal punching, before the Green Code.

According to the figures released by various parties, tencent's anti-epidemic health code has accumulated a total of 1.6 billion person-times, covering 300 cities in 20 provinces, and the health code supported by Alibaba Cloud has been distributed to 24 provinces and more than 200 cities. With the introduction of the health code across the country, it is becoming more and more relevant to everyone's life.

Before the advent of the health code, data were collected mainly by various units and the procedures were cumbersome, while the travel of community personnel was based on paper passes and there was a risk of cross-infection. The purpose of health code is to improve the efficiency of resuming work and production, which greatly improves the convenience of data collection.

But at the same time, the usefulness of Health Code is also questioned in the process of implementation. On Weibo, questions have been raised about the health code's "misjudgment, " "too much confusion, " "poor execution, " and "untrue information. ". The Health Code has gone viral, and there are a lot of hidden troubles behind it.

###Why is the Code Red?

Almost every day on Weibo, people report that their health code has an unusual color.

Ms Xu, a Hangzhou resident, is one of them. Her Epidemic Prevention Information Code found that the Health Code Red Because of the "China Mobile Interface judgment. ". According to her roaming information, she also visited Ensch while she was in her hometown in Jishou. Operator customer service explained to her that Jishou was adjacent to Ensch and that she had received a signal from Ensch, which led to the decision.

After complaining to the operator, Ms Xu's error location was changed, but after 4 days, the colour of the health code has not changed, so she is still in isolation. She has tried to report problems through the mayor's hotline and Alipay customer service, but nothing has been resolved.

After the red code was found, Ms Xu was admitted to a hotel in Hangzhou isolation for 14 days, is still in isolation. She is the owner of a clothing store, which has been quarantined so she can not open and has to pay her rent.

Ms Xu is not alone. Under the topic of "Health Code Turns Red" , many citizens report that their health code turns red without any reason, causing their work life to be affected.

A netizen from Tianjin claimed that he had been living at home, but the health code turned red because the operator had made a wrong location. Another said he had been returning to Hangzhou from Wenzhou, a key epidemic area in Zhejiang Province, for 21 days and had been displaying the green code until one day it suddenly turned red, he was forced to be quarantined and he still did not know why, while his family showed the Green Code.

The Standard of judging red, yellow and green codes varies from place to place. As far as Hangzhou is concerned, the judging criteria are mainly related to three dimensions: one is the spatial dimension, the degree of epidemic risk in one's area; two is the time dimension, the number of times one has visited the epidemic area and the length of time one has spent there; and three is the interpersonal dimension, the state of being in close contact with someone, etc. These metrics are quantified and scored, resulting in a Tricolor Code.

According to figures released by the Hangzhou government, nearly 30,000 people applied for a health code review four days after the Hangzhou Health Code went online. The color of the Health Code may be updated if it is determined that there is no abnormal behavior, and it is advised to wait patiently, officials said.

Ms Xu is still waiting for the health code to turn Green. "I agree with the community's policy of isolating high-risk people for the sake of public safety, " she told interface news. But I don't think it's appropriate to use the colour of the health code as the sole criterion for judging risk. We have to bear the cost of our mistakes."

Chinasoft international was involved in the construction of the City Health Code System in this outbreak. Jia pixing, president of its data service line, told interface news that the health code is defined according to the rules of the local government for key surveillance personnel in the epidemic prevention, such as identification: used to take the flight, bullet train, family or residential community there are confirmed or suspected cases, according to large data for objective analysis and judgment.

"As long as the data are objective, the decision logic is correct, the system execution is objective, if there is a miscarriage of justice, the main problem is the accuracy of the original data. For example, people in Jiangxi near the border of Hubei Province May, from the point of view of the track of the operator, misjudge the roaming problem of the base station as Hubei, and this kind of problem can be changed by voluntary declaration." Said Jia Pi Xing.

Pan Helin, executive director of the Zhongnan University of Economics and Law, said in an interview with interface news that the government should introduce unified management rules and supporting systems for health codes in a timely manner, not only should they be told what kind of quarantine measures to take, but they should also be told why health codes "turn red" , improve the accuracy of data matching, reduce the "accidental injury rate" , and avoid turning health codes into opaque black boxes.

###One man, six yards

More unmisjudged health code users are stumped by different regions, platforms, and names.

February 23, Wuhan in the city to implement the "health code" real name authentication management. Since then, Wuhan Resident Tang Yulin has applied for four different "electronic certificates" , namely, Hubei Health Code of Wechat, Wuhan Health Code of Alipay, National Epidemic Prevention Information Health Code and Community Electronic Pass Card.

What do different health codes do? According to the official explanation of Wuhan Health Commission, the most significant difference of these health codes lies in the scope of application —————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————— -- Mutual recognition can be realized in the whole province. The community electronic pass is mainly used in Wuhan residential area access management.

Tang Yulin told interface news that even if she had already applied for Wuhan Health Code, she would have to apply for another community electronic pass to enter the community. In addition, in order to be able to open in Wuhan after returning to Guangzhou to work, but also registered in Guangdong Province, "Yue Kang Code" and Guangzhou City, "Sui Kang Code" , each day in a different software to punch a card.

"Many people in Wuhan, including me, have relaxed and reported their health directly without taking their temperature, " Tang said, "There are too many codes to punch in, and sometimes you miss them, and you don't know which code is useful to you. "

It is not a unique phenomenon in Hubei and Wuhan that a citizen has to apply for five or six health codes for different needs such as travel and returning to work. Just in Jiangsu Province, there are more than 10 different health codes, such as Nanjing "Ninggui" , Suzhou "Sucheng Code" and Wuxi "Xikang Code" .

The main reason behind this is that health codes are not yet mutually recognized.

In response, Yang Wenzhuang, director of the population and Family Department of the National Health Commission, has publicly responded that there are three main reasons why health codes can not be mutually recognized: Different provinces have different risk levels, response levels and Prevention and control requirements; The criteria for generating health codes vary from place to place; health codes can only prove the patient's condition at the time, and subsequent health can not simply be judged on that basis.

Shaanxi, for example, requires people who have close contact with a confirmed case to be given a red code within 14 days, while Heilongjiang requires people who have close contact with a confirmed case, a suspected case, or an asymptomatic infected person to be given a red code.

"For the health code to work, it has to expand its sources of data, " said Xu Ke, executive director of the Beijing University of International Business and Economics. ... To create an accurate picture of an individual's illness . There is an urgent need to break down data segmentation and promote data sharing across government departments and regions on the one hand, and open government data on the other, so as to exploit the multi-dimensional value of data by social forces on the other."

The good news is that the Yangtze River Delta, Beijing-tianjin-hebei and other regions have announced plans to promote mutual recognition of health codes in the region, and Zhejiang and Henan, Shandong and Guizhou provinces have started to establish cooperation on mutual recognition of health codes. In addition, the National Government Service Platform on February 29 launched a nationwide "epidemic prevention health information code" , will gradually promote national health code exchange.

###Privacy and security are a concern

In Jia's view, the health code for the city's emergency response to the epidemic has two core values, on the one hand to help solve the problem of individuals on their own exposure history and other information asymmetry; on the other hand, to solve the problem of individuals'unwillingness to disclose their own information, and to provide convenience for epidemic prevention and control by changing health code into objective judgment.

But at the same time, health code contains too much personal information, how to ensure that this information is not abused, is also a matter of public concern.

Health codes in most cities, in addition to the information reported by individuals, are evaluated based on external access data, including trains, flight information, and tracks provided by the operators, which touch on every aspect of daily life. Since Health Code is mainly carried on platforms such as Alipay and Wechat, there are voices questioning that these citizens'privacy data will be used by the Internet giants.

There have also been rumours recently that in addition to the necessary check procedures, can not easily show the code to others, will therefore reveal personal privacy. Because before this has the code holder sends the Health Code to the friend circle and so on public occasions, also has many people to express the worry about this.

Cupisen believes that this claim is baseless.

He said that while the health code increases the data concentration, exchange and sharing of government affairs as the main body, it further increases the difficulty of information security risk prevention, but the government's government affairs data system security prevention system is relatively effective, there is still a need for continuous enhancement, and Internet Platform Health Code Services flow is only a settling of the results of the later determination, without the risk of leakage of personal original privacy data.

Regarding the privacy protection of users, alipay, as a platform, also mentioned in the Health Code Faq that the platform strictly follows the relevant laws and regulations of the country, to ensure the security and privacy of personal information provided by residents is not disclosed.

Luo Junjie, director-general of the First Department of Equipment Industry of the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology, also said recently that as a supervisory department, in the process of data analysis and use, according to the relevant laws and regulations on the protection of personal information, we will strictly implement relevant measures for data security and personal information protection, strengthen supervision and guard against data leakage, data abuse and other irregularities.

Jipixing analysis said that in the implementation of the Health Code, the role of Internet companies is on the one hand "code" service intermediary platform, but also part of the effective decision of data providers, and a large number of basic decision data or government, public utilities and traffic information.

And the fusion of these data has provided the help for the epidemic in the city management. Jia said the health code fully reflects the full integration of static government data, dynamic government and social data, based on the concept of "health code" scene data service product, it is a model of government big data service worthy of Reference and promotion in the future.
